Processes by Platform Busy Duration Legend:
CPU % (Platform): Percentage of time a process was active (i.e. the time at least one logical processor was executing the process).
Duration in ms (Platform): Total time in milliseconds that a process was active (i.e. the time at least one logical processor was executing the process overlapped execution only counts once).
CPU % (Logical): Percentage of time a process was active based on the accumulated logical processors active time normalized to 100% (i.e. divided by the number of logical processors).
Duration in ms (Logical): Total accumulated logical processor time in milliseconds that a process was active (i.e. overlapped execution time counts more than once).
CSwitches From Idle (per sec): Frequency of context switches from the idle process per second.
